==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: personal computer
<hw>personal computer</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>A computer{2} designed for use by one person
at a time; -- contrasted with shared-time computers such as a
<contr>mainframe</contr>, <contr>server</contr> or
<contr>minicomputer</contr>, which may be accessed by multiple users
each operating from a different input device (in the 1990's, usually a
terminal or personal computer). A <er>personal computer</er> typically
uses a microprocessor for its CPU.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> PC, microcomputer.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Personalism</ent>⟦br⟧
